Content":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This library uses "},{"code":"__VA_OPT__","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which is not standard C (not yet, I think)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"type":"text","text":" is provided either by the GNU C extension or by the C++ 20 Standard."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"So if you don’t have any of those,  then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"type":"text","text":" is probably not working."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"And that means the most important macroses of this library will not work for you correctly."}]}],"name":"Warning","type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"So, gotta have ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without it it’s very hard to implement recursion in macros, at least that’s what I concluded. That the most readable version"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ForEach"},{"type":"text","text":" macros and such can be achived only with this "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__VA_OPT__"},{"text":" stuff; I think it can be simulated more or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"less with standard stuff, but not worth the effor I think."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Perhaps there are other things I used here, which are not standard, but I have no idea of them"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Internal and Public Macros","anchor":"Internal-and-Public-Macros"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The separation on public and internal macroses are not very strict, meaning you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"use internal macroses as well as public ones. I just suppose public macros are gonna","type"